title: Japanese lunar lander, with NASA rideshare, to launch this month
summary: Japanese lunar lander developer ispace is in the final phases of preparations for the launch of its first lunar lander mission, a flight that will include a NASA lunar cubesat mission as a secondary payload.

title: New guidance from Space Force acquisition boss: ‘The traditional ways must be reformed’
summary: In an Oct. 31 memo, Calvelli laid out nine “space acquisition tenets” intended to drive change in the procurement of space systems

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy to loft USSF-44 on first flight in three years
summary: The world’s most powerful operational rocket, SpaceX’s Falcon Heavy, is set to take to the Florida skies for the first time in over three years. USSF-44, a US Space Force contracted flight with a classified payload and at least one rideshare satellite, is ready for launch.

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket rolls to pad for Tuesday launch, dual booster landing
summary: A SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket has rolled out to Kennedy Space Center Pad 39A for its first launch (and dual booster landing)...

title: Arianespace partners with Australian space tug startup
summary: Arianespace is exploring the compatibility of its rockets with orbital transfer vehicles being developed by Space Machines Company, an Australian startup.
